Two taxi bosses have been shot and killed within 24 hours in the Eastern Cape. Courtesy of #DSTV403 PORT ELIZABETH - Two taxi bosses have been shot and killed within 24 hours in the Eastern Cape. In the latest incident in Port Elizabeth on Tuesday, a taxi boss was shot through the window of his car as he dropped his child at school. The day before, a taxi organisation chairperson was found dead with bullet wounds in a township in Mthatha. READ: Cape Town taxi war shooting leaves four dead Eastern Cape police spokesperson Colonel Priscilla Naidu said the victim shot on Tuesday sustained gunshot wounds to his head and neck.
Police say the man was definitely targeted. No arrests have been made and a case of murder has been opened.